title: For Sale:  300 Mark V Weatherby RH Europa
postcontent: 300 Mag Weatherby the Jap models will typically have the nicest looking wood and much better metal and triggers than the German guns in 1970 Weatherby moved production to the Howa Factory in Japan. The strength of the action was never compromised- to many, fit and finish are superior to German models and compete well with the US models. Howa manufactured Mark Vs unti production was brought to the United States in 1994. Alll the parts this manufactured would be delivered to weatherby's Southgate facility where the final polishing bluing and assembly would take place the barrel and stocks were made in house by weatherby at the company Southgate facility. The Mark V action is a front lockingl push feed, bolt action repeater. The lug Arrangement allows for 54 degree bolt lift. This shorter bolt  lift allows for increased clearance between the bolt handle and any accessories such as Scopes that may be mounted on the rifle and arguably provides for faster cycling of action.

postcontent:
This is a French S.C.A.M. Md. 1835-A with a family history.  The pistol was taken by my father, a sargent in the U.S.Army, during the battle of the Bulge in Linnich, Germany after he suffered through an all-night artillery barrage.  Included are photos of him, insignias, his purple heart, the trenches, maps and the Tiger tank that blew his leg off.  The pistol was manufactured for the occupying Germans after the invationof France in 1940.  Chambered for the 7.65 French Long, this pistol is all original and there are no import markings.  The pistol is in good shape overall with the usual chipping of the baked enamel finish.  The original grips are in excellent condition without cracks or chips.It appears the pre-invasion the 1935-A made it to serial number B700.  The Germans carried on from B701 until D4550.  The serial number of this pistol is C7230A.  It is marked with Waffenenamt stamp on the left side of the frame.Also included are the spoils "Certificate", a substancial leather flap belt holster and two rounds of original ammunition.
